Do no use Unsigned32 for indexes

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Table.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Table
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Table.description: IPv6 interface configuration table. This table allows IPv6 related configuration of the corresponding IP interface.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Entry.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Entry
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP interface.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Active.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Active
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Active.description: Enable the static configured IPv6 address. The static configured IPv6 address can only be configured if a valid address has been written into 'ipv6Address' and 'prefixSize'.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesTable.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesTable
me1200IpConfigInterfacesTable.description: This is the IP interface table. When an IP interface is created it can be configured in the other tables found in this MIB.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesEntry.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesEntry
me1200IpConfigInterfacesEntry.description: Entries in this table represents IP interfaces created on the system

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Table.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Table
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Table.description: IPv4 interface configuration table. This table allows IPv4 related configuration of the corresponding IP interface.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Entry.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Entry
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP interface.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Active.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Active
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Active.description: Enable IPv4. IPv4 can only be enabled if either the dhcp client is enabled, or a valid address has been configured.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4EnableDhcpCl.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4EnableDhcpClient
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4EnableDhcpCl.description: Enable IPv4 dhcp client. Note: the dhcp client can only be enabled if there is no conflicts in the values of: ipv4Address, prefixSize, and dhcpClientFallbackTimeout

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Ipv4Address.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Ipv4Address
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Ipv4Address.description: IPv4 address. Note: Multiple interfaces may not have overlapping networks.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4PrefixSize.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4PrefixSize
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4PrefixSize.description: Prefix size of the network. Note: Multiple interfaces may not have overlapping networks.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4DhcpClientFa.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4DhcpClientFallbackTimeout
me1200IpConfigInterfacesIpv4DhcpClientFa.description: Dhcp client fallback timer. If dhcp is disabled then this object has no effect. If dhcp is enabled and the fallback timeout value is different from zero, then this timer will stop the dhcp process and assign the ipv4Address to the interface instead

me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv4Table.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv4Table
me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv4Table.description: This is the IPv4 route configuration table.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv4Entry.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv4Entry
me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv4Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents a configured route. NOTE: that a route may be configured without being active.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6Table.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6Table
me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6Table.description: This is the IPv6 route configuration table.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6Entry.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6Entry
me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents a configured route. NOTE: that a route may be configured without being active.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6NextHo.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6NextHopInterface
me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6NextHo.description: If the next-hop address is a link-local address, then the interface of the link-local address must be specified here. Otherwise this value is not used.

me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6RowEdi.name: me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6RowEditorNextHopInterface
me1200IpConfigInterfacesRoutesIpv6RowEdi.description: If the next-hop address is a link-local address, then the interface of the link-local address must be specified here. Otherwise this value is not used.

me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv4NeighbourInterf.name: me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv4NeighbourInterface

me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourEntry.name: me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourEntry
me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents an entry in the underlaying operting systems nieghbour table.

me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourInterf.name: me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourInterfaceQuery
me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourInterf.description: If 'ipAddress' is a link-local address, then the interface index where the host can be reached must be specified here, otherwise this must be set to zero.

me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourMacAdd.name: me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourMacAddress
me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourMacAdd.description: Mac address associated to the IP address

me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourInterf.name: me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourInterface
me1200IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourInterf.description: The interface which the neighbour can be reached on.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkEntry.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkEntry
me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP interface.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkOsInterfaceIn.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkOsInterfaceIndex
me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkOsInterfaceIn.description: The interface index used by the underlaying operating system.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkUp.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkUp

me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkBroadcast.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkBroadcast

me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkLoopback.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkLoopback

me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkRunning.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkRunning
me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkRunning.description: Interface is running (according to the operating system)

me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkNoarp.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkNoarp

me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkPromisc.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkPromisc

me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkMulticast.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceLinkMulticast

me1200IpStatusInterfaceDhcpClientV4Table.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceDhcpClientV4Table

me1200IpStatusInterfaceDhcpClientV4Entry.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceDhcpClientV4Entry
me1200IpStatusInterfaceDhcpClientV4Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents an instance of a DHCP client.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceDhcpClientV4Serve.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceDhcpClientV4ServerIp
me1200IpStatusInterfaceDhcpClientV4Serve.description: IP address of the DHCP server who has provided the DHCP offer.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Table.description: This table provides IPv6 status information for IP interfaces. If an interface is configured to use a DHCP client, then the address can be found here.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Entry.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Entry
me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP interface.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Prefix.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Prefix
me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Prefix.description: Prefix length of the IP address.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Tentative.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Tentative
me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Tentative.description: An address whose uniqueness on a link is being verified, prior to its assignment to an interface. A tentative address is not considered assigned to an interface in the usual sense.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Duplicated.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Duplicated
me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Duplicated.description: Indicates the address duplication is detected by Duplicate Address Detection (a.k.a. DAD). If the address is a link-local address formed from an interface identifier based on the hardware address, which is supposed to be uniquely assigned (e.g., EUI-64 for an Ethernet interface), IP operation on the interface SHOULD be disabled.

me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Detached.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Detached
me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Detached.description: Indicates this address is ready to be detached from the link (IPv6 network).

me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Nodad.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Nodad
me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Nodad.description: Indicates this address does not perform Duplicate Address Detection (a.k.a. DAD).

me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Autoconf.name: me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Autoconf
me1200IpStatusInterfaceIpv6Autoconf.description: Indicates this address is capable of being retrieved by stateless address Autoconfiguration.

me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6NextHopInterface.name: me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6NextHopInterface

me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagHost.name: me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagHost
me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagHost.description: The route is forwarding to this host (loop-back)

me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagGateway.description: The route is using a gateway as next-hop, of not set then an interface is used.

me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerConf.name: me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerConf
me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerConf.description: The route is installed as part of the user configuration.

me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerDhcp.name: me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerDhcp
me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerDhcp.description: The route is installed by a DHCP client.

me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerDynamic.name: me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerDynamic
me1200IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerDynamic.description: The route is installed by a routing protocol.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InReceives.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InReceives
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InReceives.description: The total number of input IP datagrams received, including those received in error. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInReceive.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInReceives
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInReceive.description: The total number of input IP datagrams received, including those received in error. This object counts the same datagrams as InReceives, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InOctets.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InOctets
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InOctets.description: The total number of octets received in input IP datagrams, including those received in error. Octets from datagrams counted in InReceives MUST be counted here. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInOctets.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInOctets
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInOctets.description: The total number of octets received in input IP datagrams, including those received in error. This object counts the same octets as InOctets, but allows for larger value. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InHdrErrors.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InHdrErrors
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InHdrErrors.description: The number of input IP datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including version number mismatch, other format errors, hop count exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InNoRoutes.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InNoRoutes
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InNoRoutes.description: The number of input IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InAddrError.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InAddrErrors
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InAddrError.description: The number of input IP datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., ::0). For entities that are not IP routers and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InUnknownPr.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InUnknownProtos
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InUnknownPr.description: The number of locally-addressed IP datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InTruncated.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InTruncatedPkts
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InTruncated.description: The number of input IP datagrams discarded because the datagram frame didn't carry enough data. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InForwDatag.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InForwDatagrams
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InForwDatag.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which this entity attempted to find a route to forward them to that final destination. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the incoming interface is incremented for each datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInForwDat.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInForwDatagrams
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInForwDat.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which this entity attempted to find a route to forward them to that final destination. This object counts the same packets as InForwDatagrams, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmReqds.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmReqds
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmReqds.description: The number of IP fragments received that needed to be reassembled at this interface. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these fragments were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the fragments. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmOKs.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmOKs
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams successfully reassembled. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmFails.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmFails
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmFails.description: The number of failures detected by the IP re-assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc.). Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments since some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these fragments were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the fragments. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDiscards.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDiscards
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDiscards.description: The number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDelivers.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDelivers
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDelivers.description: The total number of datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP). When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInDeliver.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInDelivers
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInDeliver.description: The total number of datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP). This object counts the same packets as ipSystemStatsInDelivers, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutRequests.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutRequests
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutRequests.description: The total number of IP datagrams that local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note that this counter does not include any datagrams counted in OutForwDatagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutReques.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutRequests
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutReques.description: The total number of IP datagrams that local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. This object counts the same packets as OutRequests, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutNoRoutes.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutNoRoutes
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutNoRoutes.description: The number of locally generated IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutForwData.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutForwDatagrams
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutForwData.description: The number of datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which it was successful in finding a path to their final destination. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for a successfully forwarded datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutForwDa.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutForwDatagrams
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutForwDa.description: The number of datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which it was successful in finding a path to their final destination. This object counts the same packets as OutForwDatagrams, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutDiscards.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutDiscards
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutDiscards.description: The number of output IP datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter would include datagrams counted in OutForwDatagrams if any such datagrams met this (discretionary) discard criterion. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragReqd.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragReqds
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragReqd.description: The number of IP datagrams that would require fragmentation in order to be transmitted. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for a successfully fragmented datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragOKs.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragOKs
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragOKs.description: The number of IP datagrams that have been successfully fragmented. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for a successfully fragmented datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragFail.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragFails

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4RefreshRate.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4RefreshRate
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4RefreshRate.description: The minimum reasonable polling interval for this entry. This object provides an indication of the minimum amount of time required to update the counters in this entry.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInOctets.description: The total number of octets received in input IP datagrams, including those received in error. me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InHdrErrors.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InHdrErrors
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InHdrErrors.description: The number of input IP datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including version number mismatch, other format errors, hop count exceeded, errors discovered in processing their IP options, etc. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InNoRoutes.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InNoRoutes
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InNoRoutes.description: The number of input IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InAddrError.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InAddrErrors
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InAddrError.description: The number of input IP datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., ::0). For entities that are not IP routers and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InUnknownPr.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InUnknownProtos
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InUnknownPr.description: The number of locally-addressed IP datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InTruncated.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InTruncatedPkts
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InTruncated.description: The number of input IP datagrams discarded because the datagram frame didn't carry enough data. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InForwDatag.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InForwDatagrams
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InForwDatag.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which this entity attempted to find a route to forward them to that final destination. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the incoming interface is incremented for each datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInForwDat.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInForwDatagrams
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInForwDat.description: The number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which this entity attempted to find a route to forward them to that final destination. me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmReqds.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmReqds

Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmFails.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmFails
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmFails.description: The number of failures detected by the IP re-assembly algorithm (for whatever reason: timed out, errors, etc.). Note that this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments since some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these fragments were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the fragments. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InDiscards.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InDiscards
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InDiscards.description: The number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but were discarded (e.g., for lack of buffer space). Note that this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InDelivers.name: me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InDelivers
me1200IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InDelivers.description: The total number of datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP).
